# Kiro IDE — workspace .kiro/ is version-controlled (specs, steering, hooks).
# Only ignore the local settings directory which contains user-specific config
# like MCP server connections. Global user-level config lives at ~/.kiro/ and
# is outside the repo.
#
# References:
#   Specs:    https://kiro.dev/docs/specs/best-practices/#how-do-i-share-specs-with-my-team
#             "Specs are designed to be version-controlled [...] Store specs
#              directly in your project repository alongside the code."
#   Steering: https://kiro.dev/docs/steering/#workspace-steering
#             "Workspace steering files reside in your workspace root folder
#              under .kiro/steering/"
#   Steering best practices: https://kiro.dev/docs/steering/#best-practices
#             "Treat steering changes like code changes - require reviews"
.kiro/settings/

# kiro-mem local state (if tests/dev ever write here)
.kiro-mem/
